# âœ… **FULL WORKING SOLUTION (HTML + CSS)**

---

# ðŸ”¹ **HTML**

```html
<button class="tooltip" aria-label="More information">
  Hover or focus me
  <span class="tooltip-text">This is a responsive tooltip with a dynamic width.</span>
</button>
```

---

# ðŸ”¹ **CSS**

```css
.tooltip {
  position: relative; 
  cursor: pointer;
  border: none;
  background: #444;
  color: white;
  padding: 10px 14px;
  border-radius: 5px;
  font-size: 16px;
}

/* The tooltip bubble */
.tooltip .tooltip-text {
  position: absolute;
  left: 50%;
  bottom: 125%;  /* place above button */
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  
  background: #222;
  color: #fff;
  padding: 8px 12px;
  border-radius: 6px;
  white-space: normal;     /* allow variable-length text */
  width: max-content;
  max-width: 250px;        /* tooltip responds to text length */
  
  opacity: 0;
  pointer-events: none;
  transition: opacity .25s ease;
  
  /* visually hide until hover/focus */
  visibility: hidden;
}

/* Tooltip Arrow */
.tooltip .tooltip-text::after {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  top: 100%;  /* attach to bottom of tooltip bubble */
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  
  border-width: 6px;
  border-style: solid;
  border-color: #222 transparent transparent transparent;
}

/* Show tooltip on hover and keyboard focus */
.tooltip:hover .tooltip-text,
.tooltip:focus .tooltip-text,
.tooltip:focus-visible .tooltip-text {
  opacity: 1;
  visibility: visible;
}
```

---

# âœ… **Explanation (Interview-Ready)**

---

## **1. Tooltip Container â†’ `position: relative`**

This allows the tooltip bubble to be positioned **absolutely inside the button**.

```css
.tooltip {
  position: relative;
}
```

---

## **2. Tooltip Bubble â†’ `position: absolute`**

Place above the trigger element:

```css
.tooltip-text {
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 125%;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
}
```

âœ” Centered
âœ” Positioned above
âœ” Auto-sizes to content (`width: max-content`)

---

## **3. Tooltip Arrow Using `::after`**

The arrow is just a triangle using CSS borders:

```css
.tooltip-text::after {
  border-width: 6px;
  border-style: solid;
  border-color: #222 transparent transparent transparent;
}
```

The top border is colored â†’ forms a downward-pointing arrow.

---

## **4. Show on Hover + Focus (Accessibility)**

```css
.tooltip:hover .tooltip-text,
.tooltip:focus .tooltip-text,
.tooltip:focus-visible .tooltip-text {
  opacity: 1;
  visibility: visible;
}
```

âœ” Works with mouse
âœ” Works with keyboard tab
âœ” Works with screen readers (`aria-label` recommended)

---

## **5. Tooltip Resizes With Text**

```css
width: max-content;
max-width: 250px;
white-space: normal;
```

âœ” Tooltip grows automatically for long text
âœ” Wraps gracefully
âœ” Doesn't overflow screen

